<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="100" type="decisions for synonymy">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="100">Decisions for synonymy.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="100">
The results of DNA analyses of specimens from across the complete geographical range indicated that there is only one banded 
<taxonomicName lsidName="(Notomegilla)" pageId="21" pageNumber="100" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Notomegilla">Notomegilla</taxonomicName>
species. Uncorrected sequence divergence was found to be 0-3.05%, which is below the usual limits for conspecific individuals. Moreover, there was no geographical pattern in the sequence variation. No morphological differences, other than colour variation, were found when 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rayment’s">Rayment's</normalizedToken>
syntypes were examined. Variations in the genitalia as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="21" pageNumber="100">Rayment (1944)</bibRefCitation>
appear to be due to different focal distances and angles of the drawings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="100">
We agree with 
<bibRefCitation pageId="21" pageNumber="100">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Brooks’s">Brooks's</normalizedToken>
(1988)
</bibRefCitation>
decision to synonymise 
<taxonomicName lsidName="luteola" pageId="21" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="luteola">luteola</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName lsidName="tinsleyella" pageId="21" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="tinsleyella">tinsleyella</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName lsidName="chlorocyanea" pageId="21" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="chlorocyanea">chlorocyanea</taxonomicName>
. Both Sichel (1869) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell, TDA" pageId="55" pageNumber="134" url="https://doi.org/10.1080/03745480509442880" year="1905">Cockerell (1905)</bibRefCitation>
have incorrectly referred to this species as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Anthophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthophora cingulata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata">Anthophora cingulata</taxonomicName>
(Fabr.)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="100">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="100">
This species superficially resembles several 
<taxonomicName lsidName="(Zonamegilla)" pageId="21" pageNumber="100" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Zonamegilla">Zonamegilla</taxonomicName>
species, but can be distinguished by the blue/green iridescent pubescence on the fore and mid legs; females by the completely black paraocular areas and a large, dense, medial spot of pale pubescence on T5 (Fig. 25); and males by a smooth unmodified surface of S5 and medially interrupted hair bands on T4-T6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
