<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="103" type="variation">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="103">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="103">About 10% of specimens have enough orange pigmentation to make the tergal bands and scutal hair orange and the hair of the legs pale orange. A larger number of specimens have almost white tergal bands, presumably as a consequence of wear.</paragraph>
